HEADWORD: Fratricide
<hw>Frat"ri*cide</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>fratricidium</ets> a brother's murder, fr. <ets>fratricida</ets> a
brother's murderer; <ets>frater</ets>, <ets>fratris</ets>, brother +
<ets>caedere</ets> to kill: cf. F. <ets>fratricide</ets>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of one who murders or kills his own
brother.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <ety>[L. <ets>fratricida</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>fratricide</ets>.]</ety> <def>One who murders or kills his own
brother.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

